WEBVTT

00:00:11.760 --> 00:00:13.760
Every day you have to walk the dog.

00:00:13.760 --> 00:00:15.360
Don't be scared.

00:00:15.360 --> 00:00:16.960
Say please.

00:00:16.960 --> 00:00:18.260
And thank you.

00:00:18.260 --> 00:00:20.760
Oh, thank you God, there's a nickel in it.

00:00:20.760 --> 00:00:21.760
A virgin.

00:00:22.760 --> 00:00:25.560
New York won 24 hours a day.

00:00:25.560 --> 00:00:28.060
We take the time to do it right.

00:00:28.060 --> 00:00:29.260
Debbie Faerich.

00:00:29.260 --> 00:00:30.760
The interesting thing about Mother Hale

00:00:30.760 --> 00:00:34.560
is that when you become close to a story like that

00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:38.560
and you see the difference they have made,

00:00:38.560 --> 00:00:40.760
you think that things can be okay.

00:00:40.760 --> 00:00:44.260
She believed the way to heal was to give babies what they needed most.

00:00:44.260 --> 00:00:45.760
Love and attention.

00:00:45.760 --> 00:00:47.260
24 hours a day.

00:00:47.260 --> 00:00:49.260
We take the time to do it right.

00:00:49.260 --> 00:00:52.260
New York won because there's only one New York.

00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:56.330
If you think these tunes are classics,

00:00:56.330 --> 00:00:58.330
wait till you read these.

00:00:58.330 --> 00:01:00.330
It's true top tunes are timeless,

00:01:00.330 --> 00:01:02.830
but a good book is never a thing of the past.

00:01:02.830 --> 00:01:05.330
There's nothing like a good book, I always say.

00:01:05.330 --> 00:01:08.330
Right, so ask your parents to read you one of their favorites

00:01:08.330 --> 00:01:10.830
because books are better when they're read together.

00:01:10.830 --> 00:01:14.830
Tune in to Reading, a message from the National Center for Family Literacy

