00:07:11.040 --> 00:07:12.040
Gets up for lunch,

00:07:12.040 --> 00:07:14.040
watches the Perry Mason rerun,

00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:15.040
and takes a nap.

00:07:15.040 --> 00:07:16.040
Then it's time for people's court

00:07:16.040 --> 00:07:17.040
a little dinner and...

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:18.040
Another nap?

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:21.040
No, then it's pretty much bedtime.

00:07:22.040 --> 00:07:23.040
Well, it's not like I've scheduled

00:07:23.040 --> 00:07:24.040
bungee jumping, Sam.

00:07:25.040 --> 00:07:27.040
Besides, their idea of an aerobic workout

00:07:27.040 --> 00:07:30.040
is shuffling the cards before another round of rummy.

00:07:30.040 --> 00:07:32.040
Yeah, my grandpa loves to play cards, too.

00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:34.040
We play for pretzel sticks.

00:07:34.040 --> 00:07:35.040
It's always...

00:07:35.040 --> 00:07:37.040
quit eating the pot, Tike.

00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:38.040
Tike?

00:07:38.040 --> 00:07:40.040
It's his dumb pet name for me.

00:07:41.040 --> 00:07:42.040
Put it there, Tike.

00:07:42.040 --> 00:07:43.040
How ya doin', Tike?

00:07:44.040 --> 00:07:45.040
I'm permanently fixed in his brain

00:07:45.040 --> 00:07:47.040
as being four years old.

00:07:47.040 --> 00:07:48.040
They enjoy babying you.

00:07:48.040 --> 00:07:49.040
They're grandparents.

00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:51.040
It's part of their job description.

00:07:51.040 --> 00:07:52.040
No kidding.

