Listen, I still get a few moves left, yeah.

00:10:41.710 --> 00:10:43.710
I can't believe you guys played basketball.

00:10:43.710 --> 00:10:45.710
Oh, we're not full court.

00:10:45.710 --> 00:10:48.710
Slowpoke here can't handle my fast break.

00:10:51.710 --> 00:10:53.710
Well, what's the matter?

00:10:53.710 --> 00:10:55.710
Why is everybody so quiet?

00:10:55.710 --> 00:10:57.710
Somebody die around here?

00:10:57.710 --> 00:10:58.710
I'm famished.

00:10:58.710 --> 00:10:59.710
Come on, Amelia.

00:10:59.710 --> 00:11:00.710
Let's go wash up for dinner.

00:11:00.710 --> 00:11:02.710
Last one up the stairs buys a Gatorade.

00:11:02.710 --> 00:11:03.710
Oh, you're off.

00:11:03.710 --> 00:11:11.690
I have just one question, Dad.

00:11:11.690 --> 00:11:13.690
What's that, sport?

00:11:13.690 --> 00:11:16.690
What have those people done with our real grandparents?

00:11:17.690 --> 00:11:22.000
I'm sorry about the pot roast mix-up, Janet.

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:24.000
Oh, well, I could have prepared a vegetarian banquet

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:27.000
if only I'd known you'd given up red meat.

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:29.000
And caffeine.

00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:30.000
And sugar.

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:32.000
And white flour.

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:35.000
Oh, toxins.

00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:37.000
That's what they are.

00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:38.000
Those things will kill you.

00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:41.000
Nana, Papa, what happened to you?

00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:42.000
Clarissa?

00:11:42.000 --> 00:11:44.000
No, I'd like an answer to that too, hon.

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:47.000
It's just that you both seem so...

00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:49.000
Well, go ahead and say it.

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:51.000
Young.

00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:53.000
We feel marvelous.

00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:54.000
Sure do.

00:11:56.000 --> 00:11:58.000
This is too weird.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:00.000
You guys aren't the same people who sent me

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:02.000
my first subscription to the Wall Street Journal.

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:03.000
Yeah, Dad.

00:12:03.000 --> 00:12:05.000
I mean, you didn't act like this before you were retired.

00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:06.000
Yeah.

00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:07.000
Guy knew what to expect then.

00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:08.000
What went wrong?

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:09.000
Well, I'll tell you.

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:11.000
For 42 years I ran my factory.

00:12:11.000 --> 00:12:13.000
And all we ever made was those little

00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:16.000
press-on nose pads for eyeglasses.

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:18.000
So boring!

00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:21.000
So we were really looking forward to our golden years.

00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:23.000
Time to play cards.

00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:25.000
Yes, and watch old movies.

00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:27.000
Look at the birds.

00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:28.000
Sounds great.

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:30.000
Was it great?

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:32.000
He was driving me up the wall.

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:34.000
But he couldn't sit still.

00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:36.000
It was depressing.

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:37.000
Then it hit me.

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:39.000
Last June we were playing cards.

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:42.000
I hate Jen Rummy.

00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:45.000
To tell the truth, I always hated Jen Rummy.

00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:48.000
But I only played it because he liked it.

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:51.000
That's when we decided to live a little.

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:53.000
And we've been on the go ever since.

00:12:53.000 --> 00:12:55.000
Well, I think that's wonderful.

00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:57.000
I think it's awful.

00:12:57.000 --> 00:13:00.000
I mean, I'm...awful nice.

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:03.000
I think it's, you know, I think it's...

00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:05.000
Hey.

00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:08.000
I think I'd better replay my week.

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:11.000
Well, out with the old and in with the new.

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:14.000
It's great to see you can get older without getting slower.

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:17.000
The only thing is, if they keep up this pace,

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:19.000
who knows what will happen?

00:13:19.000 --> 00:13:22.000
Will their search for adventure have a scaling new height?

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:28.080
Will their knick-knack collection meet a little more zip?

00:13:28.080 --> 00:13:41.760
Or will they become international spies?

00:13:41.760 --> 00:13:43.760
Boiling plots for global domination.

00:13:46.760 --> 00:13:48.760
I thought I'd have to set the pace for them,

00:13:48.760 --> 00:13:51.760
but now it looks like they're setting the pace for me.

00:13:51.760 --> 00:13:53.760
And my whole family.

00:13:53.760 --> 00:14:00.880
What a week.

00:14:00.880 --> 00:14:03.880
It's been nonstop ever since my grandparents got here.

00:14:03.880 --> 00:14:05.880
We spent Monday at the water park,

00:14:05.880 --> 00:14:07.880
Tuesday at the blues festival,

00:14:07.880 --> 00:14:09.880
Wednesday night's square dancing,

00:14:09.880 --> 00:14:11.880
and today it was Wismos Arcade.

00:14:11.880 --> 00:14:15.880
We've got blown away, soaked, trampled, and blasted.

00:14:15.880 --> 00:14:20.450
In fact, aside from my grandparents,

00:14:20.450 --> 00:14:22.450
I'm the only one still standing.

00:14:22.450 --> 00:14:24.450
Cheap watch.

00:14:24.450 --> 00:14:26.450
I can't believe the prizes they give out.

00:14:26.450 --> 00:14:28.450
It does nothing it's supposed to.

00:14:28.450 --> 00:14:30.450
You stooge. It's a two-dollar watch.

00:14:30.450 --> 00:14:32.450
It's supposed to. It broke.

00:14:32.450 --> 00:14:40.950
Am I holding the keys?

00:14:40.950 --> 00:14:42.950
Oh, good. I wasn't sure.

00:14:42.950 --> 00:14:46.950
I've lost all feeling to my arm after four straight hours of ski ball.

00:14:46.950 --> 00:14:49.950
Well, no one can say you're not a good sport, Marshall.

00:14:49.950 --> 00:14:51.950
What has happened to my parents?

00:14:51.950 --> 00:14:53.950
I mean, I can't get over the change.

00:14:53.950 --> 00:14:56.950
Remember when they came to visit last year?

00:14:56.950 --> 00:15:00.950
We spent the whole week doing that 900-piece jigsaw puzzle

00:15:00.950 --> 00:15:02.950
of a covered bridge.

00:15:02.950 --> 00:15:04.950
Ah, those are the days.

00:15:04.950 --> 00:15:06.950
See you then.

00:15:06.950 --> 00:15:08.950
I'm great to see the Belmondos again, huh?

00:15:08.950 --> 00:15:11.950
Oh, still, the same old friend and baby.

00:15:11.950 --> 00:15:15.950
Oh, and they're so excited about the party Saturday night.

00:15:15.950 --> 00:15:17.950
Saturday night?

00:15:17.950 --> 00:15:19.950
What party Saturday night?

00:15:19.950 --> 00:15:22.950
Crossing your grandparents' anniversary party.

00:15:22.950 --> 00:15:25.950
I thought that was on the 18th.

00:15:25.950 --> 00:15:28.950
Saturday is the 18th, Brainiac.

00:15:28.950 --> 00:15:31.950
Uh-oh. You have plans?

00:15:31.950 --> 00:15:36.950
Uh, well, I was just gonna go see Pearl Jam.

00:15:36.950 --> 00:15:39.950
Well, you can invite your friend Pearl to the party.

00:15:39.950 --> 00:15:41.950
Oh, yeah.

00:15:41.950 --> 00:15:43.950
So we still have our DJ.

00:15:43.950 --> 00:15:47.740
Yeah, you can count on me.

00:15:47.740 --> 00:15:49.740
Any special requests?

00:15:49.740 --> 00:15:52.740
Well, um, my favorite band is Vanilla Fudge.

00:15:52.740 --> 00:15:55.740
How can you listen to that stuff?

00:15:55.740 --> 00:16:04.240
Decisions, decisions.

00:16:04.240 --> 00:16:06.240
There's so much music to choose from

00:16:06.240 --> 00:16:08.240
when you're trying to please three generations.

00:16:08.240 --> 00:16:11.240
I guess one thing I won't be hearing is Pearl Jam.

00:16:11.240 --> 00:16:13.240
But Sam's tickets were crummy anyway.

00:16:13.240 --> 00:16:15.240
There'll be other concerts.

00:16:15.240 --> 00:16:17.240
Hi, Sam.

00:16:17.240 --> 00:16:21.480
Hey, Clarissa. Guess what?

00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:22.480
What?

00:16:22.480 --> 00:16:24.480
My dad came through for us.

00:16:24.480 --> 00:16:26.480
It seems the music editor really wanted basketball tickets,

00:16:26.480 --> 00:16:28.480
only my dad could get hold of.

00:16:28.480 --> 00:16:29.480
So?

00:16:29.480 --> 00:16:30.480
So?

00:16:30.480 --> 00:16:34.480
Pearl Jam, fourth row, center.

00:16:34.480 --> 00:16:36.480
He totally scored.

00:16:36.480 --> 00:16:38.480
Fourth row?

00:16:38.480 --> 00:16:39.480
Fourth row from the stage?

00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:41.480
Yeah, can you believe it?

00:16:41.480 --> 00:16:44.480
This is gonna be one totally awesome event.

00:16:44.480 --> 00:16:48.110
One totally awesome event too many.

00:16:48.110 --> 00:16:50.110
Now what am I gonna do?

00:16:50.110 --> 00:17:03.540
More Clarissa. More Snake.

00:17:03.540 --> 00:17:05.540
After this.

00:17:21.540 --> 00:17:23.540
And why should the people listen to you?

00:17:23.540 --> 00:17:25.540
Unlike some other Robin Hoods,

00:17:25.540 --> 00:17:28.540
I can speak with an English accent.

00:17:28.540 --> 00:17:30.540
A Mel Brooks film.

00:17:30.540 --> 00:17:32.540
The legend had it come.

00:17:32.540 --> 00:17:33.540
Rated PG-13.

00:17:33.540 --> 00:17:35.540
Now playing at theaters everywhere.

00:17:35.540 --> 00:17:38.540
This morning we were regular fifth graders.

00:17:38.540 --> 00:17:39.540
Now we're heroes.

00:17:39.540 --> 00:17:41.540
Get on started when we were separated

00:17:41.540 --> 00:17:43.540
from our class on a field trip.

00:17:43.540 --> 00:17:45.540
We were off goofing around when we realized

00:17:45.540 --> 00:17:46.540
we're late.

00:17:46.540 --> 00:17:47.540
We're gonna miss our bus.

00:17:47.540 --> 00:17:49.540
We knew if we missed our bus, we'd be toast.

00:17:49.540 --> 00:17:52.540
Once we saw our bus, we figured we were aces.

00:17:52.540 --> 00:17:53.540
We were wrong.

00:17:53.540 --> 00:17:54.540
How come we don't know anyone?

00:17:54.540 --> 00:17:55.540
Who's bus?

00:17:55.540 --> 00:17:56.540
Because that's our bus.

00:17:56.540 --> 00:17:58.540
What bus are you boys supposed to be on?

00:17:58.540 --> 00:18:00.540
The one that's going to McDonald's.

00:18:00.540 --> 00:18:01.540
Yeah.

00:18:01.540 --> 00:18:02.540
Follow that bus.

00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:03.540
Not with famous.

00:18:03.540 --> 00:18:04.540
Which is cool.

00:18:04.540 --> 00:18:05.540
Because famous people never do homework.

00:18:05.540 --> 00:18:07.540
Get out of the roundhouse.

00:18:07.540 --> 00:18:08.540
Boom.

00:18:08.540 --> 00:18:09.540
Having a ball throw rehearsal.

00:18:09.540 --> 00:18:10.540
Change.

00:18:10.540 --> 00:18:11.540
Change.

00:18:11.540 --> 00:18:12.540
Change.

00:18:12.540 --> 00:18:33.060
It's just a snip.

00:18:33.060 --> 00:18:42.410
Hi Chris, it's mom.

00:18:42.410 --> 00:18:44.410
Look honey, I've got a lot of work to do.

00:18:44.410 --> 00:18:46.410
So I won't be home until late again.

00:18:46.410 --> 00:18:47.410
Just do the usual.

00:18:47.410 --> 00:18:49.410
You know, fix yourself a little something.

00:18:49.410 --> 00:18:50.410
Anything you want.

00:18:50.410 --> 00:18:52.410
Oh, and I left some money for you on the counter.

00:18:52.410 --> 00:18:54.410
Use it for whatever you like.

00:18:54.410 --> 00:18:56.410
Now, dad won't be home until Tuesday.

00:18:56.410 --> 00:18:57.410
He says hi.

00:18:57.410 --> 00:18:59.410
Oh, and somebody told me you quit soccer.

00:18:59.410 --> 00:19:00.410
Is anything wrong?

00:19:00.410 --> 00:19:02.410
Well, just leave me a note.

00:19:02.410 --> 00:19:03.410
Love you.

00:19:03.410 --> 00:19:04.410
Bye.

00:19:04.410 --> 00:19:12.570
This summer, the best way to see TNT's favorite movies

00:19:12.570 --> 00:19:16.570
is with everyone's favorite celebrities.

00:19:16.570 --> 00:19:17.570
Ta-da.

00:19:17.570 --> 00:19:18.570
This week, everyone's favorite

00:19:18.570 --> 00:19:20.570
Seinfeld Sidekick, Jason Alexander.

00:19:20.570 --> 00:19:22.570
Hosts Jason and the Argonauts.

00:19:22.570 --> 00:19:27.570
TNT's our favorite movie, summer edition 93.

00:19:27.570 --> 00:19:31.570
Thursday and Sunday on TNT.

00:19:31.570 --> 00:19:39.070
Watching.

00:19:39.070 --> 00:19:40.070
Nick!

00:19:40.070 --> 00:19:43.070
And now, back to Clarissa explains it all.

00:19:43.070 --> 00:19:54.350
I've got to choose.

00:19:54.350 --> 00:19:57.350
They're counting on me to DJ my grandparents' anniversary,

00:19:57.350 --> 00:19:59.350
which ordinarily would be cool.

00:19:59.350 --> 00:20:01.350
But then there's the best seat, the best concert,

00:20:01.350 --> 00:20:03.350
and the best band in the whole entire world.

00:20:03.350 --> 00:20:04.350
What do you do?

00:20:04.350 --> 00:20:05.350
And there are two things you really want to do,

00:20:05.350 --> 00:20:08.350
and they're both happening at the same time.

00:20:08.350 --> 00:20:09.350
Probably have tickets.

00:20:09.350 --> 00:20:10.350
Cool.

00:20:10.350 --> 00:20:11.350
Tell me about it.

00:20:11.350 --> 00:20:12.350
Fourth row.

00:20:12.350 --> 00:20:13.350
How often you get seats like that?

00:20:13.350 --> 00:20:14.350
Like never.

00:20:14.350 --> 00:20:15.350
So go.

00:20:15.350 --> 00:20:16.350
Your grandparents will understand.

00:20:16.350 --> 00:20:17.350
Besides, they're old.

00:20:17.350 --> 00:20:18.350
They probably won't even remember.

00:20:18.350 --> 00:20:19.350
I'm obligated.

00:20:19.350 --> 00:20:20.350
I'm the DJ.

00:20:20.350 --> 00:20:22.350
The success of the party will rest in my hands.

00:20:22.350 --> 00:20:25.350
And these primo tickets will rest in someone else's.

00:20:25.350 --> 00:20:27.350
They're my grandparents.

00:20:27.350 --> 00:20:28.350
They're our anniversary.

00:20:28.350 --> 00:20:30.350
I'm going to the party.

00:20:30.350 --> 00:20:31.350
Cool.

00:20:31.350 --> 00:20:35.290
Can I have your ticket?

00:20:35.290 --> 00:20:38.290
Everyone's your friend when they want something from you.

00:20:38.290 --> 00:20:39.290
Hi, Sam.

00:20:39.290 --> 00:20:43.530
Hey, Clarissa.

00:20:43.530 --> 00:20:45.530
You better sit down for this.

00:20:45.530 --> 00:20:46.530
Sam.

00:20:46.530 --> 00:20:52.720
It's your backstage passage.

00:20:52.720 --> 00:20:53.720
I know.

00:20:53.720 --> 00:20:54.720
The Pearl Jam?

00:20:54.720 --> 00:20:55.720
I know.

00:20:55.720 --> 00:20:56.720
This Saturday?

00:20:56.720 --> 00:20:57.720
I know.

00:20:57.720 --> 00:21:03.820
I love your music.

00:21:03.820 --> 00:21:04.820
Oh, that is so dorky.

00:21:04.820 --> 00:21:05.820
I know.

00:21:05.820 --> 00:21:06.820
I won't say anything.

00:21:06.820 --> 00:21:07.820
They'll just think I'm mysterious.

00:21:07.820 --> 00:21:09.820
So you'll blow up the party.

00:21:09.820 --> 00:21:12.450
Party.

00:21:12.450 --> 00:21:14.890
Can't miss this concert.

00:21:14.890 --> 00:21:16.890
I'll just have to tell them.

00:21:16.890 --> 00:21:17.890
How hard can that be?

00:21:18.890 --> 00:21:19.890
It's swollen.

00:21:19.890 --> 00:21:21.890
Oh, it's not swollen, Marshal.

00:21:21.890 --> 00:21:23.890
And it can't possibly hurt as much as you say it does.

00:21:23.890 --> 00:21:24.890
Ah, okay.

00:21:24.890 --> 00:21:26.890
You get your leg whacked by a windmill at the mini golf,

00:21:26.890 --> 00:21:28.890
and then you can talk to me about pain.

00:21:28.890 --> 00:21:30.890
Well, I just hope your leg is better by tonight

00:21:30.890 --> 00:21:33.890
because your parents are counting on all of us going roller skating.

00:21:33.890 --> 00:21:35.890
Well, you're not going to be by yourself.

00:21:35.890 --> 00:21:37.890
Fergus and Clarissa are going to be there.

00:21:37.890 --> 00:21:38.890
Darn the luck.

00:21:38.890 --> 00:21:41.890
I just realized my term paper on mollusks is due,

00:21:41.890 --> 00:21:43.890
and I'm afraid I'll have to miss roller skating.

00:21:43.890 --> 00:21:45.890
Just exactly when is it due?

00:21:45.890 --> 00:21:47.890
Well, it's due in two weeks,

00:21:47.890 --> 00:21:50.890
but when you start skimping on gastropods,

00:21:50.890 --> 00:21:52.890
you're just asking for trouble.

00:21:52.890 --> 00:21:54.890
Mm-hmm. Nice try, Ferguson.

00:21:54.890 --> 00:21:57.890
Mom, I'm tired.

00:21:57.890 --> 00:21:58.890
I ache.

00:21:58.890 --> 00:22:00.890
I have a blister on my toe.

00:22:00.890 --> 00:22:01.890
Please.

00:22:01.890 --> 00:22:04.890
Well, maybe we can talk them into a nice game of parcheasy.

00:22:04.890 --> 00:22:06.890
What do you think, dear?

00:22:06.890 --> 00:22:09.890
Oh, whatever anybody else wants to do.

00:22:09.890 --> 00:22:11.890
Something wrong?

00:22:11.890 --> 00:22:13.890
Oh, hi, everybody.

00:22:13.890 --> 00:22:17.890
But, oh, Marsha, what happened to your leg?

00:22:17.890 --> 00:22:19.890
Oh, it's nothing.

00:22:19.890 --> 00:22:20.890
You can say that again.

00:22:20.890 --> 00:22:22.890
I may have to stay off it for a few days.

00:22:22.890 --> 00:22:24.890
Oh, you're going to make roller skating, aren't you?

00:22:24.890 --> 00:22:25.890
Touch and go.

00:22:25.890 --> 00:22:28.890
Oh, my little marshmallow.

00:22:28.890 --> 00:22:30.890
Nana, Papa.

00:22:30.890 --> 00:22:32.890
Hey, how's our little disc jockey?

00:22:32.890 --> 00:22:35.890
Good. Um, about the party.

00:22:35.890 --> 00:22:36.890
It'll be a blast.

00:22:36.890 --> 00:22:38.890
We just had lunch with the Del Mondos,

00:22:38.890 --> 00:22:40.890
and they're so impressed with you.

00:22:40.890 --> 00:22:41.890
With me?

00:22:41.890 --> 00:22:42.890
That's right.

00:22:42.890 --> 00:22:44.890
Mimi can't believe a teenager

00:22:44.890 --> 00:22:45.890
would give up her Saturday night

00:22:45.890 --> 00:22:47.890
to spend time with her grandparents.

00:22:47.890 --> 00:22:49.890
It is hard to believe.

00:22:49.890 --> 00:22:51.890
But about Saturday.

00:22:51.890 --> 00:22:53.890
But we told them that our clavrissa was different.

00:22:53.890 --> 00:22:55.890
She wants to be with us.

00:22:55.890 --> 00:22:57.890
I do. I do want to be with you.

00:22:57.890 --> 00:22:58.890
Of course you do.

00:22:58.890 --> 00:23:00.890
It wouldn't be a party without you.

00:23:00.890 --> 00:23:02.890
We better get changed for roller skating.

00:23:02.890 --> 00:23:04.890
Do you want to hold these people up?

00:23:04.890 --> 00:23:05.890
Okay.

00:23:05.890 --> 00:23:12.410
Well, I'm glad I got that off my chest.

00:23:12.410 --> 00:23:16.080
What about Norman Lunrich?

00:23:16.080 --> 00:23:17.080
Norman Lunrich?

00:23:17.080 --> 00:23:20.080
You're going to give my Pearl Jam tickets to Norman Lunrich?

00:23:20.080 --> 00:23:22.080
He eats mayonnaise and peanut butter sandwiches

00:23:22.080 --> 00:23:24.080
and enjoys doing logarithms.

00:23:24.080 --> 00:23:27.080
Clavrissa, you've eliminated everybody else.

00:23:27.080 --> 00:23:29.080
Let's face it, you can't go.

00:23:29.080 --> 00:23:31.080
If it's any consolation,

00:23:31.080 --> 00:23:34.080
I'll be screaming a name when Pearl Jam kicks in at 10.

00:23:34.080 --> 00:23:36.080
10?

00:23:36.080 --> 00:23:38.080
The ticket says 8.30.

00:23:38.080 --> 00:23:40.080
We'll figure at least an hour and a half

00:23:40.080 --> 00:23:42.080
to suffer through the warm-up band.

00:23:42.080 --> 00:23:44.080
Party starts at 8.

00:23:44.080 --> 00:23:47.080
The real concert starts at 10.

00:23:47.080 --> 00:23:48.080
Oh, my gosh!

00:23:48.080 --> 00:23:49.080
What?

00:23:49.080 --> 00:23:51.080
Sam, with your help, there's still one chance

00:23:51.080 --> 00:23:53.080
I can jam with Pearl Jam.

00:23:57.990 --> 00:24:00.990
Well, sure you might think $5 is a bit pricey

00:24:00.990 --> 00:24:03.990
for a chocolate bar, but it's for the chess team,

00:24:03.990 --> 00:24:05.990
and we need our uniforms.

00:24:05.990 --> 00:24:08.990
In that case, here you go, Sonny.

